# Product & Order System Walkthrough

I have migrated the application to a dynamic, database-driven architecture using MongoDB.

## 1. Product System
- **Models**: Created [Product](file:///c:/Users/Adonis/Downloads/App/src/types.ts#10-29) schema with fields for features, stock, and pricing.
- **API**: Full CRUD endpoints at `/api/products`.
- **Frontend**: 
    - [Shop.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Adonis/Downloads/App/src/pages/Shop.tsx) fetches live products.
    - [AdminDashboard.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Adonis/Downloads/App/src/pages/AdminDashboard.tsx) allows creating, updating, and deleting products.
    - Resolved type mismatches (Tags vs Features).

## 2. Order System (New Feature)
- **Models**: Created [Order](file:///c:/Users/Adonis/Downloads/App/src/types.ts#48-57) schema to track user purchases.
- **API**: implemented `/api/orders` to list and manage orders.
- **Frontend**: 
    - [AdminDashboard.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Adonis/Downloads/App/src/pages/AdminDashboard.tsx) now fetches **real-time orders** from the database instead of using mock data.
    - Order statuses ([Pending](file:///c:/Users/Adonis/Downloads/App/src/pages/AdminDashboard.tsx#27-38), `Completed`, `Paid`) are now tracked in the DB.

